name: Stuff-for-sale
body:
***

## Mac Airport Express (1st Generation)

**$60** -- [Here are the technical specs](http://support.apple.com/kb/SP1) and this is the [unboxing](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Y-8HO81f51Q) for a more detailed review.

![Mac Airport Express1](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-sH5O746TLiM/UktHGSpHTKI/AAAAAAAAC64/U3WOASvzimg/w657-h1168-no/20131002_071400.jpg)
![Mac Airport Express 2](https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-ybscP27Giy8/UktHGeooh1I/AAAAAAAAC64/TldETIAIX8Q/w657-h1168-no/20131002_071409.jpg)
![usage](http://1.bp.blogspot.com/_5bjgyFe53o0/TR2pN49EBqI/AAAAAAAAAJc/whUhNnMI5fI/s1600/overview_expressathome_20080115.jpeg)

## Thermaltake Sorprano mid tower (computer case)

**Free** -- The original [product page](http://support.thermaltakeusa.com/Product.aspx?C=1433&ID=1448) has information on bays, dimensions, etc.

![Thermaltake Sorprano tower](https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-Y-cJf3OKh9s/UktHGZ-Zk2I/AAAAAAAAC64/N1lTjzOF4A8/w958-h539-no/20131002_071428.jpg)

## Samsung Galaxy S2

**$100** -- Camera is scratched, other than that good condition

![Samsung Galaxy S2](https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-i-xd5TChcmE/UktHGZGFZ4I/AAAAAAAAC64/0403Du7g-N0/w958-h539-no/20131002_071626.jpg)

## Filco Cherry MX Red (mechanical keyboard)

**$70** -- Fantastic keyboard, once you move to a mechanical keyboard it's hard to go back. It makes typing a pleasure. [Why are these awesome?](http://peterhallam.com.au/which-mechanical-keyboard-switch-should-i-get-cherry-mx-red-keyswitch/)

![keyboard](https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-QjVaOsjHtJA/UktHGedyNRI/AAAAAAAAC64/XAHGl3Q320g/w958-h539-no/20131002_071613.jpg)

## Logitech USB Controller (dual action)

**$10** -- Product review [here](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=e1zeBaASgXE)

![usb controller](https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-yiWLx1DKZoM/UktHGecsBoI/AAAAAAAAC64/q-QmGadlpb4/w958-h539-no/20131002_071559.jpg)

## Asus O!Play HDP-R1 (media player)

**$40** -- Play movies from your computer on your TV!. [Product review here](http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=k6WJZmNm8Ws)

![oplay back](https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-wAh7qHNLNxU/UktHGbjdz4I/AAAAAAAAC64/4zB0ehIOO44/w958-h539-no/20131002_071527.jpg)

![oplay front](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-hgMPZgl7sgA/UktHGcm6cOI/AAAAAAAAC64/886rBmW3e50/w958-h539-no/20131002_071512.jpg)

## Powered USB hub

**FREE**

![usb hub](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-IPpQTtGQyjE/UktHGVsE4nI/AAAAAAAAC64/jeMPymV5vdA/w958-h539-no/20131002_071656.jpg)

## Telstra Elite Pre-Paid Mobile Wifi unit

**$40** -- Great for when your on the move and want internet. [Product manual here](http://www.telstra.com.au/internet/download/document/getting-started-guide-elite-prepaid.pdf)

![wifi hotspot](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-ewNbWUb1bK0/UktHGSl2qWI/AAAAAAAAC64/50dFakmvq-4/w958-h539-no/20131002_071708.jpg)

## KVM Switch (VGA)

**$5** -- Use to swap between two computers while keeping the same keyboard, mouse & monitor.

![kvm switch](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-_ExTJemQmAE/UktHGaHrCrI/AAAAAAAAC64/XSN8ADXF-Gk/w657-h1168-no/20131002_071720.jpg)

## Gold plated S-Video cable (5M)

**$5**

![svideo cable](https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-UpfPqPinBus/UktHGX1ezZI/AAAAAAAAC64/-zK_T1mM_3U/w657-h1168-no/20131002_071729.jpg)

## Nexus 7 16B (tablet)

**$200** -- Great for the kids, watch movies or play games on those long road trips. [Product page here](http://www.google.com.au/nexus/7/)

![nexus7](https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-Y8Kdl1yXdLI/UktHGUOm0UI/AAAAAAAAC64/PA874-kSeoc/w657-h1168-no/20131002_071751.jpg)

## Wireless N USB Adapter (DWA-140)

**$20** -- Boost the wifi capability of some of your devices at home. [Product page](http://www.dlink.com/us/en/home-solutions/connect/adapters/dwa-140-wireless-n-usb-adapter)

![wireless dongle front](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-TG_f8Q08HXk/UktHGWltPnI/AAAAAAAAC64/0ZzlJPDrXFA/w657-h1168-no/20131002_071922.jpg)

## D-Link Boxee Box

**$80** -- Amazing media player for your TV, stream content from your home computer or the internet. [More info here](http://www.dlink.com.au/boxee/more.html)

![boxee](https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-Xt6_74hgHg4/UktHGVJWnrI/AAAAAAAAC64/rXB6BdfpRxM/w657-h1168-no/20131002_071934.jpg)

## Gel Mouse pad / Keyboard rest

**$3ea** - Stop those aches and pains!

![mouse](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-1IDb04khX2I/UktHGVSQHMI/AAAAAAAAC64/lzpB8VFr6Ak/w958-h539-no/20131002_072148.jpg)

![keyboard](https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/-5Su0aCwOGsA/UktHGQx6vWI/AAAAAAAAC64/Goccl9k6eps/w958-h539-no/20131002_072158.jpg)

## JVC Hifi Stereo system

**$100** -- Two speakers and one subwoofer, has an iPod/iPhone dock and remote. Also has CD & aux in

![stereo](https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/-ThSZHaVRsS0/UktHGbyAQYI/AAAAAAAAC64/Dfkt1OqdIi4/w657-h1168-no/20131002_072100.jpg)

## Thecus NAS n7700+ with 7x2TB HD

**$700 ono** -- This won't be for everyone, sits on your network and hosts your media, setup with RAID so you don't have to worry about losing precious data.

![nas](https://plus.google.com/u/0/photos/112530270150154168912/albums/5929911511351552289/5929911510535327282?pid=5929911510535327282&oid=112530270150154168912)
![open nas](https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-1VceScrLBbM/UktHGf_2-hI/AAAAAAAAC64/BzE9DhIJJHQ/w657-h1168-no/20131002_072043.jpg)

## D-Link gigabit switch

2x 5 port **$25** -- [info here](http://www.dlink.com.au/products/?pid=229)
1x 8 port **$30** -- [info here](http://www.dlink.com.au/products/?pid=230)

![5port](https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-_O-fE9JjBA8/UktHGapB8wI/AAAAAAAAC64/rwJamsE2ebg/w958-h539-no/20131002_072020.jpg)

## D-Link Wireless N router

**$50** -- [info here](http://www.dlink.com.au/products/?pid=565)

![router](https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-r7QH-gz-bGw/UktHGc-zvwI/AAAAAAAAC64/nKtpntNIlKY/w958-h539-no/20131002_071959.jpg)

## Logitech Harmony 900 - universal remote

**$150** -- An ergonomic universal remote with a full-color touch screen that lets you control your all your devices with one remote. [More info here](http://www.officeworks.com.au/retail/products/Technology/Home-Entertainment/Universal-Remotes/INLOG3847)

![remote](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-LskM_BsFIyc/Uk3jsLOiEPI/AAAAAAAAQrQ/zJWe3QpjBKo/w657-h1168-no/20131003_065410.jpg)


## Media center

**$400** -- Custom built home media center, installs Windows Media Center and your good to go. Runs in complete silence. Comes with 2 controllers, one for the case and one for the TV car.

Parts: 
- 1 Scythe 120mm S-FLEX 800rpm Fan
- 1 Antec Fusion Remote Black
- 1 Western Digital Green 2TB WD20EARS
- 1 64GB SSD
- 1 Corsair CMV4GX3M2A1333C9 4GB (2x2GB) DDR3
- 1 Leadtek WinFast DTV2000DS Dual HD Tuner
- 1 Seasonic X-400 Fanless Gold 400W
- 1 ASUS E35M1-M PRO Motherboard

![media center](https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/-CKuQUGHKVqs/Uk3jsFYVdcI/AAAAAAAAQrQ/WZ4zUMRTNco/w958-h539-no/20131003_065358.jpg)
